{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 03:37:02.363895", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and goal\\n- Topology: 2-tier pod with super-spine (AS 65000), spines (65100/65101), and leaves (65200/65201). Hosts: pc_0_0 (via leaf_router_0_0) and pc_0_1 (via leaf_router_0_1).\\n- Objective: Assess network health, detect anomalies, localize faults, and identify root cause.\\n\\nSummary of findings\\n- Control plane (BGP) is healthy across all routers: all EBGP sessions are Established with expected prefix counts.\\n- Data plane anomaly impacting the 10.0.0.0/24 leaf segment on leaf_router_0_0: host pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) is unreachable, including failure to reach its default gateway (10.0.0.1).\\n- Root cause: a misconfigured static blackhole route on leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.0/30 -> Null0) combined with advertising 10.0.0.0/30 causes longest-prefix-match to drop packets destined for 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3, including pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2). This explains loss of all traffic to/from pc_0_0 despite BGP health.\\n\\nDetail and evidence\\n\\n1) Reachability tests\\n- get_reachability results show widespread success between other hosts but anomalies for pc_0_0 (e.g., “status: unknown” in multiple tests involving pc_0_0).\\n- Direct host checks:\\n  - From pc_0_0: ping 10.0.0.1 (its gateway) → 100% loss.\\n  - From pc_0_1: ping 10.0.1.1 (its gateway) → OK.\\n  - Inter-host:\\n    - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: timeout.\\n    - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: timeout.\\n- Conclusion: Isolation is specific to the 10.0.0.0/24 segment (pc_0_0 side). The 10.0.1.0/24 segment (pc_0_1) functions normally.\\n\\n2) Control plane (BGP) health\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 8 neighbors up; State/PfxRcd ~31 per spine neighbor.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 8 neighbors up; State/PfxRcd ~32 per spine neighbor.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 12 neighbors up; receives 2 prefixes from 172.16.1.1 (leaf 0_0) and 1 prefix from 172.16.1.3 (leaf 0_1), which matches leaf 0_0 advertising both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.0.0/30, and leaf 0_1 advertising 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 12 neighbors up; consistent view.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): all spine sessions Established; wide set of prefixes; consistent ECMP towards pods.\\n- Conclusion: BGP adjacencies and routing dissemination are normal; the issue is not control-plane.\\n\\n3) Device/segment localization\\n- The fault impacts only the segment served by leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - pc_0_1’s gateway reachable, but pc_0_0’s gateway not.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 has no anomalies and no static blackhole in config.\\n  - Therefore, localize the problem to leaf_router_0_0’s handling of 10.0.0.0/24.\\n\\n4) Routing tables and configuration (root-cause evidence)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 running-config:\\n  - ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0\\n  - address-family ipv4: network 10.0.0.0/24 and network 10.0.0.0/30\\n- leaf_router_0_0 FIB (show ip route):\\n  - C>* 10.0.0.0/24 is directly connected, eth8\\n  - S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole)\\n- leaf_router_0_1 FIB:\\n  - B>* 10.0.0.0/30 via 172.16.1.2 (learned from leaf 0_0), confirming propagation of the more-specific.\\n- Interface counters on leaf_router_0_0 (eth8 = 10.0.0.1/24):\\n  - RX packets 15, TX packets 3 (very low TX, consistent with locally generated responses being dropped before egress).\\n- Effect of blackhole /30 on leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - Longest-prefix-match selects 10.0.0.0/30 over connected 10.0.0.0/24 for destinations 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3.\\n  - Packets originating from the leaf to pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) are discarded locally, including ICMP echo replies to pc_0_0. This causes pc_0_0’s pings to its gateway to fail (no replies).\\n  - Remote-to-10.0.0.2 traffic learned via the BGP /30 will also be dropped at the leaf due to the blackhole.\\n\\nAssessment and impact\\n- Anomaly: Yes. Data-plane reachability failure for 10.0.0.0/30 addresses on leaf_router_0_0’s segment, most notably pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2).\\n- Faulty device: leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Root cause: Misconfiguration — static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/30 present on leaf_router_0_0 and advertised; it supersedes the connected 10.0.0.0/24 for destinations within 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3, blackholing host-bound traffic.\\n- Blast radius: Any traffic to/from 10.0.0.0/30 (10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3) is affected. In this lab, pc_0_0 at 10.0.0.2 is isolated. Other parts of the fabric and host segments (e.g., 10.0.1.0/24) operate normally.\\n\\nRelevant outputs (highlights)\\n- pc_0_0 → 10.0.0.1: 100% loss\\n- pc_0_1 → 10.0.1.1: OK\\n- leaf_router_0_0 FIB: S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole); C>* 10.0.0.0/24 on eth8\\n- leaf_router_0_0 config: ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0; network 10.0.0.0/30 and 10.0.0.0/24 advertised\\n- BGP across fabric: Established, expected prefix counts; spines learn 10.0.0.0/30 from leaf 0_0 as intended by that misconfiguration.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The network’s control plane is healthy and converged, but data-plane traffic for the 10.0.0.0/30 range is intentionally dropped on leaf_router_0_0 due to a static blackhole route that overlaps the connected host subnet. This single configuration defect on leaf_router_0_0 is the root cause of pc_0_0’s unreachability and explains all observed symptoms., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c75d0f99-89de-4dbb-8137-08827880c113'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
